Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{1%lb} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%oz} lengthwise; slice 
crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Finely dice @celery{2.5%oz}. Halve, peel, and finely 
chop @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Strip @thyme{¼%oz} leaves from stems; roughly 
chop leaves. Roughly chop @parsley{¼%oz}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring 
to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @butter{2%tbsp}, and 
@thyme leaves{1%tsp}(chopped) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of water as needed. 
Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until next step.

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} 
(preferably ovenproof, pan) over medium-high heat. Add carrot; season with salt and pepper. 
Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add celery, onion, and a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, 
until veggies are just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in @garlic powder{1%tsp} and @thyme{1%tsp}(chopped); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @organic ground beef{10%oz} to pan with veggies and season with salt and pepper. 
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1%unit} and @flour{1%tbsp}; cook, stirring, until thoroughly combined, 
~{1%minute}.

> Swap in organic beef for beef.

Gradually pour @water{½%cup} into pan with beef mixture. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{2} 
and bring to a boil. Cook until mixture is very thick, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in half the parsley. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a baking dish.

Top beef filling with an even layer of mashed potatoes, leaving a gap around edge of pan. 
Evenly sprinkle with @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}.

Broil until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Sprinkle with remaining parsley and serve directly from pan.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.